heap  -HARD DISK-> high memory,slow process
      -heap very safe,cant access without knowing exact address
stack -RAM-> low memory,high speed


program has 3 areas
 code section
 stack(16 gb like that)
 heap(128 gb like that)
always in a program num,i,j,count,a[100] all stores in stack by default
normal variable-static
poniter variable-dynamic

1D array
 declaration
 initialization
 accessing
Declaration
 static -normal variable
 dynamic-poniter variable

 arr[0]=address of array+(0*mem byte of variable)
 arr[1]=address of array+(1*mem byte of variable)
 arr[2]=address of array+(2*mem byte of variable)
 arr[3]=address of array+(3*mem byte of variable)

 eg:
 2x2 array:
 1 2
 3 4
 1000 1004 1008 1012
 1    2    3    4
 arr[0]=1000+0*4=1000
 arr[1]=1000+1*4=1004


dynamic-
 adv:
  extend size
  free the memory
  vast memory
malloc-garbage value-declaration
calloc-0 is stored in all elements of array while declaration
realloc-extend size of already declared array
free-free up the memory

SYNTAX:
malloc
 int *a[]=(int*)malloc(n*sizeof(int));
  return type void
  so typecasting(int) at beginning
calloc-contiguous [CONTINUOUS] allocation
 int *a[]=(int*)calloc(n,sizeof(int)); // comma*********
realloc
   a[]=realloc(a,n*sizeof(int));
free
 free(a);
